\begin_layout Standard
For numerical models where the conserved scalar and vector fields are known
 throughout the domain, the geometric parameters of the vortex arise straightfor
wardly from the first and second areal moments of vorticity.
 Each of these moments is normalized by the total circulation.
 Following Saffman 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Saffman1970"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and integrating in the local neighborhood of the vortex in axisymmetric
 cylindrical coordinates,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\Gamma & =\iint\omega\dd{r}\dd{z}\label{eq:Gamma_vortex}\\
R & =\frac{1}{\Gamma}\iint\omega r\dd{r}\dd{z}\\
R_{2}^{2} & =\frac{1}{\Gamma}\iint\omega r^{2}\dd{r}\dd{z}\\
z_{c} & =\frac{1}{\Gamma}\iint\omega z\dd{r}\dd{z}\label{eq:z_vortex_center}
\end{align}

\end_inset

From Archer 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Archer2008"
literal "false"

\end_inset

