 radius is approximately
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
a^{2}=(R_{2}^{2}-R^{2})\label{eq:vortex_a_squared}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When a numerical model does not include the vortex formation process, the
 steady-state vortex-induced velocity field must instead be determined by
 first positing the vorticity distribution in the core.
 The simplest case, depicted in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Vortex-induced-velocity"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

